er with an otherworldly rainbow of colors, illuminating the damp, slime-coated walls with a bizarre, unsettling beauty.,A large, ornate tapestry, now tattered and decaying, hangs limply on one wall, its faded image depicting a forgotten battle or a lost civilization's glory.,The floor is disturbingly slick with fresh, dark ichor, leaving a glistening trail that leads ominously away into a shadowed, unexplored passage.,A peculiar, bone-deep chill descends, colder and more pervasive than the damp stone, as if a spectral presence has just passed directly through you, leaving an icy void.,Scattered tools and discarded mining equipment-pickaxes, shovels, empty ore bags-suggest recent, hasty excavation work, abandoned for unknown reasons.,A low, constant buzz fills the air, emanating from all directions at once, as if from a thousand unseen insects or some hidden, organic hive.,The walls are ominously lined with empty, broken display cases and pedestals, their former treasures long since plundered or vanished, hinting at past glories and losses.,A single, massive, rusted chain hangs precariously from the ceiling, its immense length disappearing into a black, unfathomable abyss far below, hinting at untold depths.,The faint, coppery smell of iron mixed with stale blood is palpable, clinging to the air like a shroud, a grim reminder of violence that recently occurred here.,An unnerving silence falls, so complete it feels heavier than any sound, pressing in on your ears and creating a disorienting sense of auditory deprivation.,Flickering arcane sigils, seemingly burned into the very stone of the floor, still emit a faint wisp of smoke and a subtle magical hum, a lingering arcane presence.,A broken sarcophagus lies disturbingly open, its heavy lid askew, revealing only a thick layer of undisturbed dust within, its ancient occupant long gone or never truly there.,The air is thick with the pervasive smell of damp earth mingled with ancient mildew, a musty, acrid odor that permeates everything and speaks of forgotten time.,A strange, shimmering pool of liquid, impossibly clear yet too viscous to be mere water, ripples gently in the center of the room, reflecting light in bizarre patterns.,A chaotic pile of splintered wooden planks suggests either a recent structural collapse or a frantic, desperate attempt to barricade a passage, now violently breached.,The distinct, nauseating scent of burnt hair and singed flesh wafts disturbingly from an unexplored passage, indicating a recent, gruesome, and fiery event.,A crude mosaic on the floor depicts a distorted, alien landscape, its unsettling imagery causing a slight, persistent dizziness and a feeling of unreality.,The distant, rhythmic clang of a hammer on an anvil echoes from somewhere far off, suggesting a hidden forge or a workshop operating deep within the dungeon's core.,A faint, phosphorescent glow emanates from deep, narrow cracks in the stone floor, hinting at strange mineral deposits or perhaps unseen, luminous creatures beneath.,The air is surprisingly fresh, carrying the clean scent of pine and damp earth, as if you are unexpectedly close to a surface entrance or a hidden, underground forest.,A series of small, glowing eyes seem to peer out from tiny crevices in the walls, tracking your movements for a moment before vanishing abruptly into the darkness.,The entire room feels subtly but undeniably tilted, creating a disorienting effect and making it difficult to maintain your balance as you move through the space.,A faint, sweet melody, almost like a forgotten lullaby, drifts gently from an unseen source, strangely beautiful yet profoundly out of place and unnerving.,The rough stone walls are crudely covered in ancient, unsettling drawings depicting grotesque figures engaged in violent hunts and macabre ceremonies, defaced by time.,A shimmering pile of glittering, unidentifiable dust lies inexplicably in the center of the room, catching the faint light and shimmering with a subtle, internal luminescence.,A constant, soft murmur of voices seems to echo just beyond the threshold of hearing, never quite resolving into distinct words, creating a persistent, unsettling auditory illusion.,A thick, suffocating layer of volcanic ash covers everything, crunching audibly underfoot with every step you take, coating the room in a fine, grey powder.,The distant, mournful creak of unseen timbers groans from the ceiling above, a foreboding sound that suggests the dungeon's ancient structure is slowly succumbing to decay.,A specific section of the floor radiates an unusual, persistent warmth, hinting at geothermal activity, a hidden magma chamber, or a powerful magical heat source concealed beneath.,A small, intricately crafted music box lies tragically broken on the floor, its delicate mechanisms shattered, its once-beautiful tune forever silenced, a poignant end to its melody.,The walls are disturbingly slick with a strange, oily residue that glistens ominously in the dim light, leaving a greasy film on anything it touches, and a sense of unnatural sliminess.,A faint, putrid stench of stagnant water mixed with something unidentifiable fills the air, a truly nauseating combination that assaults your senses and makes you instinctively recoil.,A massive, overturned stone table dominates the room, its immense weight implying a violent upheaval or a titanic struggle that left it toppled and shattered, a silent witness to chaos.,The air is unnaturally charged with static electricity, causing your hair to visibly prickle and stand on end, a peculiar and unsettling sensation hinting at a lingering arcane discharge.,A series of perfectly circular holes dot the walls with unnerving precision, as if bored by something immense and precise, their purpose a complete enigma that fills you with wonder and dread.,The sound of a single, slow drip of water from an unknown source echoes with unnerving regularity, each isolated drop amplifying the chamber's silence and counting out the passing moments.,A discarded, bloodied adventurer's pack lies open on the floor, its contents-rusted tools, torn maps, dried rations-strewn tragically about, a chilling testament to a desperate and failed expedition.,The floor is dangerously uneven, covered in countless loose rocks and debris that shift and clatter with every step you take, making cautious movement a constant, noisy challenge.,A strange symbol, glowing with a faint, unsettling purple light, is painted crudely on the far wall, its alien design radiating an arcane energy that feels both powerful and malevolent.,The air tastes distinctly of metal and fear, a bitter, coppery tang on your tongue that speaks of blood and ancient dread, a visceral sensation that sets your nerves on edge.,A small, almost imperceptible flickering light can be seen through a distant, narrow crack in the wall, hinting at another, unknown chamber, drawing you deeper into the dungeon's labyrinth.,The walls are entirely coated in a thick, velvety moss, unnaturally soft and spongy, that seems to dampen all sound, creating an oppressive quiet that presses in on your ears.,A broken weapon-perhaps a chipped axe head, a splintered spear, or a rusted sword hilt-lies abandoned and forgotten on the floor, a relic of a past conflict now lost to time.,The air here is unnaturally still and heavy, as if time itself has somehow slowed or paused within this particular space, creating a disorienting sensation of suspended animation.,A faint, disembodied laugh, chillingly cold and utterly devoid of mirth, echoes briefly through the chamber, then vanishes abruptly, leaving you to wonder if you truly heard it.,The remnants of a powerful explosion-scorched stone, splintered rock, and a lingering smell of sulfur-have scarred one section of the chamber, hinting at sudden, destructive force.,A set of rusted manacles hangs from a low ceiling, swaying slightly in a phantom breeze, perhaps a lingering memory of past imprisonment or torture that haunts the empty space.,The floor is entirely covered in small, sharp shards of something crystalline, hard and glittering, that crunch ominously underfoot with every step you take, threatening to cut through your boots.,A low, guttural snarl seems to emanate from the very shadows, just beyond your line of sight, a primal sound that promises unseen danger and unnerves you to your core.,A peculiar draft carries the distinct scent of something sweet and decaying, a truly unsettling combination that grows stronger as you breathe, making your stomach churn.,The rough stone walls are riddled with countless tiny holes, from which small, unseen, beady eyes seem to watch your every move, unblinking and constantly observing.,A single, ancient goblet, made of tarnished silver and intricately engraved, rests untouched on a high, unreachable ledge, glinting faintly in the gloom, a tantalizing mystery.,The air is thick with the potent scent of ozone mixed heavily with the acrid smell of burning arcane reagents, a powerful, almost overwhelming aroma of recently released magic.,A shallow pool of strangely warm, red liquid stains the center of the room, reflecting the dim light like solidified blood, its unsettling nature making you hesitate to approach.,The constant, distant thrum of colossal machinery can be distinctly felt vibrating through the very stone of the dungeon, a deep, relentless rhythm from some unseen, vast engine.,A faint, ethereal glow emanates from deep within the narrow cracks in the floor, pulsating softly and invitingly, hinting at hidden energies or strange, luminous life below.,The air is so oppressively dry it makes your throat ache and your skin feel taut, as if all moisture has been violently sucked from the atmosphere, a dehydrating pressure.,A set of raw, enormous claw marks, larger than any beast you know, are gouged deeply into the stone walls, appearing freshly carved and suggesting an incredibly powerful creature.,A broken statue of an unknown, grotesque beast lies in countless pieces, its features contorted in silent agony, a fallen idol or guardian defeated in a long-forgotten battle.,The floor is covered in a strange, shimmering, almost unearthly dust that seems to cling stubbornly to your boots, leaving a faint, glittering trail with every step you take.,A chilling, almost imperceptible whisper constantly brushes against your ear, so faint it's almost imaginary, yet it persists, hinting at dark secrets or unseen presences.,The distant, echoing sound of heavy footsteps grows slowly louder, filling the chamber with dread, then abruptly stops, leaving an eerie, profound silence in its wake.,A small, perfectly carved wooden bird, impossibly delicate and light, rests incongruously on a fallen pillar, a delicate anomaly in this brutal environment, seeming almost out of place.,The rough stone walls are lined with numerous niches, each holding skeletal remains, their empty eye sockets staring out into the chamber like silent, eternal witnesses to all who pass.,A faint, sickly green luminescence pulses softly from something hidden just behind a loose stone in the wall, a soft, unnatural glow hinting at something strange and possibly dangerous beyond.,A large, ominous shadow flickers briefly across the far wall, as if something massive and unseen has just moved, leaving you with a profound sense of unease and anticipation.,A series of small, perfectly round holes are drilled into the stone floor, their purpose unknown but clearly deliberate, suggesting a hidden mechanism or a forgotten trap.,A faint, almost imperceptible vibration runs through the floor, as if the very stone is alive and breathing, a subtle reminder of the dungeon's ancient, pulsing heart.,A large, intricately carved stone door stands ominously at the end of the passage, its surface covered in strange, glowing runes that pulse with a faint, unsettling light.,A thick, oppressive fog clings to the floor, swirling lazily around your ankles and making it difficult to see more than a few feet ahead, creating an eerie, claustrophobic atmosphere.,A series of small, delicate footprints, perhaps from a child or a small creature, lead mysteriously through the dust, vanishing abruptly at the edge of a darkened corner.,A faint, almost imperceptible hum of energy resonates through the air, a low, constant vibration that seems to emanate from the very walls, hinting at hidden power or ancient magic.,A large, rusted iron gate blocks the passage ahead, its heavy bars creaking ominously with every slight movement, suggesting it has not been opened in a very long time.,A small, intricately carved stone figurine lies abandoned on the floor, its features worn smooth by time, yet still exuding a strange, unsettling aura that makes you hesitate to touch it.,A faint, ghostly light flickers in the distance, illuminating a narrow passageway that seems to lead deeper into the dungeon, beckoning you with its eerie glow.,A series of large, jagged teeth marks are deeply embedded in the stone wall, suggesting a massive creature recently passed through, leaving its terrifying mark on the dungeon's structure.,A thick, heavy mist clings to the floor, swirling lazily around your feet and making it difficult to see more than a few feet ahead, creating an eerie, claustrophobic atmosphere.,A faint, almost imperceptible, metallic taste lingers in the air, a subtle reminder of the dungeon's ancient, rusting iron and the countless battles fought within its walls.,A large, intricately carved stone pedestal stands in the center of the room, its surface covered in strange, glowing runes that pulse with a faint, unsettling light.,A faint, ghostly light flickers in the distance, illuminating a narrow passageway that seems to lead deeper into the dungeon, beckoning you with its eerie glow.,A chilling breeze sweeps through the chamber, carrying with it the faint, unsettling scent of decay and something unidentifiable, making your skin crawl.,A fine layer of shimmering, almost iridescent dust coats every uneven surface, catching the scarce light and scattering it into fleeting, ghostly motes.,The air is unnaturally heavy and still, thick with the pervasive scent of damp, ancient earth and the faint, unsettling musk of unseen, creeping things.,A faint, rhythmic scratching, subtle yet persistent, seems to emanate from deep within the unseen cracks and hollows of the very stone walls, just beyond your hearing's grasp.,Clumps of bioluminescent moss, a sickly, vibrant green, cling tenaciously to the damp, sweating stone, casting an ethereal, unsettling glow that distorts the cavern's true shape.,Ancient, heavily rusted shackles, their iron links thick with centuries of corrosion, dangle menacingly from the low, crumbling ceiling, clinking softly with any breath of air.,A low, continuous hum, almost imperceptible to the ear but felt as a vibration in your teeth, resonates through the cold, unforgiving floor, hinting at hidden mechanisms or arcane energies.,Puddles of murky, perfectly stagnant water lie scattered across the uneven flagstones, reflecting the meager light like shattered, obsidian mirrors, their shallow depths unsettlingly opaque.,The profound and eerie silence is punctuated only by the relentless, solitary drip of water from an unseen fissure, each echoing plink amplifying the oppressive stillness of the chamber.,Faded, crude pictographs of distorted, alien figures engaged in bizarre, long-forgotten rituals are scrawled across one crumbling section of the wall, their malevolence still palpable.,A massive, impassable heap of splintered timbers and shattered masonry indicates a catastrophic collapse, forever blocking whatever secrets or paths lay beyond that ruined section of the passage.,The air carries a faint, sickly sweet scent, cloying and unsettlingly organic, reminiscent of decaying flowers mingled with something far more sinister and unidentifiable.,Glimmers of moisture, like dew on a spiderweb, cling to every surface, making the cold, rough stone walls appear to weep silently and perpetually.,From somewhere far off, a chilling, drawn-out wail, mournful and primal, reverberates through the deep, subterranean passages, a sound that chills you to the bone.,A discarded, rusted pickaxe, its wooden handle rotted away, lies half-buried in a mound of loose, damp earth, a poignant and silent testament to a forgotten, desperate struggle.,The floor slopes gently but relentlessly downwards, hinting at an inexorable descent into deeper, older, and perhaps more terrifying levels of the endless dungeon below.,A strange, cold draft, carrying the faint scent of distant, ancient ice and stagnant, unmoving air, snakes insidiously around your ankles, leaving a lingering, bone-deep chill.,A scattering of small, unnervingly pristine skeletal remains, bleached white and unidentifiable, lies haphazardly in a shadowed corner, starkly hinting at past struggles and a gruesome, overlooked end.,The rough stone walls are deeply scarred with brutal, savage gouges, as if something gargantuan and razor-clawed had recently passed through with destructive intent.,A single, unlit torch, its cloth wrapped tight and its wood dry with age, remains wedged precariously in a corroded metal bracket on the wall, a silent sentinel.,A faint, high-pitched scurrying and chittering, like a thousand tiny claws on stone, suggests a hidden, teeming colony of unseen creatures burrowing within the walls.,An intricate pattern of dark, unsettlingly viscous, and undeniably ancient stains mars a significant section of the cold, unyielding floor, their gruesome origin a complete mystery.,The air feels unnaturally thick and profoundly still, almost suffocating in its oppressive silence, as if all sound has been violently swallowed by the oppressive darkness.,A single, unnervingly perfectly spherical stone rests inexplicably in the exact center of the room, as if deliberately placed there by an unknown hand, its perfect form a complete enigma in the rough dungeon.,The coppery, metallic tang of old, dried blood, now faint but distinct, clings stubbornly to the heavy, stale air, a grim and visceral reminder of violence long past.,A vast, ancient spiderweb, spun thick and glistening like spun glass, stretches with incredible resilience across an entire doorway, a fragile but unyielding curtain that has defied the passage of countless ages.,A peculiar chill, colder and more pervasive than the dungeon's usual dampness, seems to settle exclusively in one specific corner of the room, radiating an unseen coldness.,Numerous, shattered fragments of ancient pottery, some painted with faded, enigmatic designs, litter the cold floor, silent, fragile remnants of something violently destroyed.,The constant, soft whisper of imperceptible air currents hints at unseen openings, massive caverns, or vast, unexplored spaces beyond your immediate perception.,A faint, sweet perfume, utterly out of place in this grim environment, drifts languidly on the stagnant air, strangely alluring yet profoundly unsettling, hinting at either forgotten beauty or a cunning trap.,Faded, intricate etchings depicting a celestial map of alien constellations, twisted and unfamiliar, adorn sections of the crumbling walls, glowing with a soft, ethereal light.,The floor tilts subtly but undeniably downwards, creating a disorienting sensation of unbalance and hinting at a deeper, more treacherous descent into the dungeon's abyssal, unknown depths.,A skeletal hand, its ancient bones bleached to an unnatural white and its fingers splayed, protrudes eerily from a mound of loose, dark rubble, a grim, silent greeting.,The very air is thick with dust, disturbed by your entrance, swirling in lazy currents and catching the dim light, making it difficult to discern distant details clearly.,A peculiar, rhythmic thumping sound, like a slow, heavy heartbeat, vibrates persistently through the very floor, a deep, unsettling pulse from the dungeon's unseen core.,Small, perfectly smooth pebbles are scattered across the floor, worn round by the passage of countless unseen feet or the relentless flow of ancient subterranean currents.,The faint, ghostly murmur of voices, almost human-like, seems to drift on the absolute edge of hearing, never quite resolving into distinct words, an unsettling auditory illusion.,A discarded, tattered piece of ancient cloth, its vibrant color long since faded to a dull gray, is snagged on a sharp rock, a poignant, forgotten remnant of a past traveler.,The room seems to softly pulse with a low, barely perceptible light, a faint, internal luminescence emanating from unseen cracks or hidden, glowing mineral deposits."

# --- HAZARDS ---
hazard collapsing_ceiling
    description "Cracks spiderweb across the ceiling, and dust rains down."
    effect_message "Dust and debris fall around you! You take {damage} damage."
    damage 15
end hazard

hazard noxious_gas_cloud
    description "A strange, green mist hangs heavy in the air, burning your eyes."
    effect_message "You cough and your eyes water from the gas! You take {damage} damage."
    damage 20
end hazard

hazard thorny_vine_trap
    description "Thick, thorny vines suddenly lash out from the walls!"
    effect_message "The vines scratch and pull at you, but you manage to break free, albeit with a few new scrapes. You take {damage} damage."
    damage 10
end hazard

# --- PUZZLES ---
puzzle riddle_puzzle
    name "riddle of the forgotten sage"
    type "riddle"
    description "A stone tablet with ancient runes glows faintly. A voice whispers: 'I have keys but open no locks. I have space but no room. You can enter, but you can't go outside. What am I?'"
    solution "keyboard"
    reward_xp 50
    reward_gold 25
    reward_items "silver_key,100;greatsword_of_shadows,5;super_healing_potion,50"
    fail_penalty_type "damage"
    fail_penalty_value 20
    fail_penalty_message "The statue rumbles and sends a shockwave through you! You take {value} damage."
end puzzle

puzzle riddle_of_the_ancient_guardian
    name "riddle of the ancient guardian"
    type "riddle"
    description "An ancient stone statue blocks the path. Its eyes glow faintly, and a voice echoes in your mind: 'I speak without a mouth and hear without ears. I have no body, but I come alive with wind. What am I?'"
    solution "echo"
    reward_type "item"
    reward_data "silver_key"
    fail_penalty_type "damage"
    fail_penalty_value 20
    fail_penalty_message "The statue rumbles and sends a shockwave through you! You take {value} damage."
end puzzle

puzzle lever_puzzle
    name "lever puzzle"
    type "mechanism"
    description "A pedestal stands in the center of the room with three ornate levers: one made of **gold**, one of **silver**, and one of **bronze**. A plaque reads: 'The path forward lies in the metal of kings. Pull the right lever.'"
    solution "gold"
    reward_type "item"
    reward_data "rusty_key"
    fail_penalty_type "monster_spawn"
    fail_penalty_monster_name "lurking_shadow_beast"
    fail_penalty_message "You pull the wrong lever! A lurking shadow beast emerges from the darkness!"
end puzzle

puzzle statue_puzzle
    name "statue's offering"
    type "item_delivery"
    description "A dusty old statue with an outstretched hand, seeming to crave sustenance."
    target_name "statue"
    required_item "healing_item"
    reward_type "item"
    reward_data "bone_key"
    fail_penalty_type "flavor"
    fail_penalty_message "The statue remains impassive, seemingly disappointed."
end puzzle

# --- ITEM SPAWN WEIGHTS ---
define item_spawn_weights "backpack,0.05;shield,0.15;armor_body,0.15;armor_cloak,0.10;weapon,0.15;consumable_healing,0.25;consumable_other,0.10;key,0.05;default,0.05"

# --- KEY UNLOCK EVENTS ---
define key_unlock_rusty "Guardian of the Rusted Chest"
define key_unlock_silver "Silver Golem"

# --- SOUNDS ---
define ambient_music "sounds/infinitedungeonambience.wav"
define combat_music "sounds/infinitedungeoncombat.wav"
define inn_music "sounds/infinitedungeoninn.wav"
define vendor_music "sounds/infinitedungeonvendor.wav"